- Please be seated.

33:24.002 --> 33:27.875
- Next on the docket,
Finley v. Broder.

33:27.918 --> 33:29.442
Is everybody here?

33:29.485 --> 33:30.747
- Your Honor, Keri Allen

33:30.791 --> 33:32.140
representing
the City of Chicago.

33:32.184 --> 33:33.881
We were first up
on the docket after lunch.

33:33.924 --> 33:36.623
- Were on the docket.
Not anymore.

33:36.666 --> 33:38.103
- What?
Why?

33:38.146 --> 33:40.105
- Well, that's a question
for one of your colleagues.

33:40.148 --> 33:41.932
Someone from
the mayor's office called

33:41.976 --> 33:43.586
and said the matter
had been settled.

33:43.630 --> 33:45.762
- Now, would the parties
from the case I called

33:45.806 --> 33:47.416
please approach the bench?

33:47.460 --> 33:48.896
Thank you.

33:50.680 --> 33:53.857
- ♪ Coming
out of the woodworks ♪

34:01.822 --> 34:03.563
- You've got some nerve.

34:03.606 --> 34:04.999
Hijacking my meeting
is one thing,

34:05.043 --> 34:06.827
but hanging me out to dry
in court is another.

34:06.870 --> 34:09.438
That affects my reputation
and that I won't stand for.

34:09.482 --> 34:10.831
- You should've thought
about reputation

34:10.874 --> 34:12.920
before you took my license.

34:12.963 --> 34:14.095
- Have you ever thought about

34:14.139 --> 34:15.444
why I took your license,
Ms. Pearson?

34:15.488 --> 34:16.967
- Oh, I know why.

34:17.011 --> 34:19.100
You're pissed because I made
your office look like shit

34:19.144 --> 34:20.928
with the 13th District case.

34:20.971 --> 34:23.757
- Wrong! You made the
13th District look like shit.

34:23.800 --> 34:25.802
My father was a police officer

34:25.846 --> 34:28.066
and he didn't go out there and
risk his life every single day

34:28.109 --> 34:31.634
so you could call him
and all other cops animals.

34:31.678 --> 34:34.115
- I didn't know
about your father.

34:34.159 --> 34:36.030
- You do now.

34:36.074 --> 34:39.120
- And I didn't
call them anything.

34:39.164 --> 34:41.992
I went after specific men
who did specific things.

34:42.036 --> 34:44.952
- Well, let me be specific
with you right now.

34:44.995 --> 34:47.955
You want to come at me,
come at me,

34:47.998 --> 34:49.783
but stay the hell away
from my department

34:49.826 --> 34:51.654
and any of the lawyers
who work for me

34:51.698 --> 34:54.788
or I'll make disbarment
feel like jaywalking.

34:54.831 --> 34:57.182
- Are you threatening me?

34:57.225 --> 34:59.184
- I'm warning you.

34:59.227 --> 35:01.142
I've been underestimated
my whole life

35:01.186 --> 35:03.101
'cause I don't look like
a policeman's daughter.

35:03.144 --> 35:05.929
But I'm 33 years old
and I'm the City Attorney.

35:07.192 --> 35:09.498
I didn't get where I am
by being stupid.

35:21.249 --> 35:22.120
- The Council
will come to order.

35:23.338 --> 35:24.600
I'll now call the role.
Alderman Blake.

35:24.644 --> 35:26.428
- Present.
- Alderman Morrison?

35:26.472 --> 35:28.256
- Present.
- Alderman Coats.

35:28.300 --> 35:31.346
- Uh, if I may before we begin,
I'd like permission to speak.

35:34.219 --> 35:37.135
As you know, I believe
a math and science education

35:37.178 --> 35:39.137
is vital to the future
of our young people.

35:39.180 --> 35:41.400
That's why I supported
the Richard Feynman School

35:41.443 --> 35:43.184
of Science and Engineering,

35:43.228 --> 35:44.533
a charter school
on the North side,

35:44.577 --> 35:47.101
to replace my ward's
aging high school.

35:47.145 --> 35:48.581
As I said,
it's a short distance

35:48.624 --> 35:50.235
for our kids to travel,

35:50.278 --> 35:52.280
but it'll take them far
in their careers.

35:52.324 --> 35:55.196
However,
in light of the community's

35:55.240 --> 35:58.199
incredible commitment
to keep Franklin open

35:58.243 --> 36:01.289
and the mayor's personal plea,

36:01.333 --> 36:05.598
I have decided to withdraw my
support for closing the school.

36:05.641 --> 36:06.816
- Yes!

36:10.211 --> 36:12.387
Please, please.
If you will.

36:14.041 --> 36:16.391
Effective immediately,
I have also decided to resign

36:16.435 --> 36:18.132
as alderman of the 54th Ward

36:18.176 --> 36:20.787
to pursue opportunities
in the private sector.

36:20.830 --> 36:23.050
It's been an honor to serve
and work with you all.

36:24.704 --> 36:26.314
What the hell is going on?

36:26.358 --> 36:27.576
I'm going to look like an idiot

36:27.620 --> 36:29.622
if I don't make some kind
of statement.

36:29.665 --> 36:31.058
- This has all the information

36:31.101 --> 36:32.668
about the alderman's
new position

36:32.712 --> 36:34.670
as well as a commitment
to rebuild schools

36:34.714 --> 36:36.368
in Kenwood
and the surrounding communities.

36:36.411 --> 36:38.631
- You knew about this?
- I did.

36:53.341 --> 36:55.125
- What do you think?

36:55.169 --> 36:58.390
Oyster White
or Charleston Blue?

36:59.826 --> 37:01.741
- I'm just curious.

37:01.784 --> 37:04.483
Since you're the one
who got her the job,

37:04.526 --> 37:05.875
what exactly is Debbie Coats

37:05.919 --> 37:07.573
going to be doing
at Midwest Portage?

37:07.616 --> 37:09.662
- She's going
to make it a priority

37:09.705 --> 37:11.359
to ramp up production

37:11.403 --> 37:15.145
and deliver your fleet
of electric buses.

37:19.237 --> 37:21.239
- You went behind my back,
Ms. Pearson.

37:21.282 --> 37:23.763
- I made you look good,
Mr. Mayor.

37:23.806 --> 37:25.721
You just ended
a 23 day hunger strike.

37:25.765 --> 37:28.333
- Did I?
I mean, the strike only ended

37:28.376 --> 37:31.249
because a greedy alderman
took a cush VP job.

37:31.292 --> 37:32.728
- And now you have 60 days
to replace her

37:32.772 --> 37:35.557
with someone who better
represents the community.

37:35.601 --> 37:38.168
You might want
to make a statement about that

37:38.212 --> 37:40.127
so the strikers know
you heard them.

37:40.170 --> 37:41.694
- You mean this.

37:41.737 --> 37:43.304
- I like that Derrick.

37:43.348 --> 37:45.785
He is on top of everything.

37:48.353 --> 37:49.745
- You know,
you may not know this,

37:49.789 --> 37:52.270
but I was the youngest alderman
ever elected.

37:52.313 --> 37:53.749
26.

37:53.793 --> 37:55.316
I'd done a whole year at
the public defender's office.

37:55.360 --> 37:57.275
I was ready
to take on the world.

37:57.318 --> 37:58.580
First month in,
I tried to raise

37:58.624 --> 38:01.322
the minimum wage to $7.25.

38:01.366 --> 38:03.411
7.25's half what it should be.

38:03.455 --> 38:06.284
You would've thought
I was a Leninist.

38:06.327 --> 38:09.548
But I didn't back down
and I pushed it through.

38:09.591 --> 38:10.766
- See, I knew
there was a dreamer

38:10.810 --> 38:12.594
hiding in there somewhere.

38:12.638 --> 38:14.640
Look where you are now.

38:14.683 --> 38:17.599
- I'm where I am right now
because right after that,

38:17.643 --> 38:20.167
the oldest member told me
what might happen

38:20.210 --> 38:23.301
if I bit off too much
too soon.

38:23.344 --> 38:25.912
- I can't tell if
that's advice or a warning.

38:25.955 --> 38:28.175
- You saved the day today,

38:28.218 --> 38:30.482
but everything we do here
has real life consequences.

38:30.525 --> 38:31.787
- You think I don't know that?

38:31.831 --> 38:33.354
- I think you're a smart woman

38:33.398 --> 38:35.878
who doesn't understand
that when shit happens,

38:35.922 --> 38:38.403
it's my name on the door,
not yours.

38:41.406 --> 38:44.757
- This is all new to me,
Mr. Mayor,

38:44.800 --> 38:46.585
and it's going
to take a little time

38:46.628 --> 38:48.630
for me to get used
to not calling the shots.

38:49.849 --> 38:52.460
But I don't think you want me
taking smaller bites.

38:52.504 --> 38:54.332
- No?
- No.

38:56.377 --> 39:00.512
- I think you have
a problem you need solved

39:00.555 --> 39:03.776
and that's why
you brought me in.

39:03.819 --> 39:06.822
Now you've seen
what I can do,

39:06.866 --> 39:09.956
why don't you tell me
what Pat McGann has on you.

39:17.442 --> 39:19.879
I'd go with the blue.

39:23.404 --> 39:30.368
A♪

39:48.734 --> 39:50.997
- Oh, Jessica!

39:52.564 --> 39:54.261
Hey, why don't you come in?

39:54.304 --> 39:56.437
- Oh, I don't think I should.

39:56.481 --> 39:57.699
- Is something wrong?

39:57.743 --> 39:59.875
Lily, I need
to tell you something

39:59.919 --> 40:02.661
that I--I should
have told you days ago.

40:04.532 --> 40:06.316
I dropped your lawsuit

40:06.360 --> 40:08.580
in exchange for a job
with the mayor.

40:09.755 --> 40:11.887
- I know.

40:11.931 --> 40:13.802
- Angela said
she didn't tell you.

40:13.846 --> 40:15.456
- She didn't have to tell me.

40:15.500 --> 40:17.763
I know when something's
going on with my daughter.

40:19.460 --> 40:22.420
- Lillian, I'm so sorry.
- Don't be sorry.

40:22.463 --> 40:25.858
But the question is why?
Why--why didn't you tell me?

40:25.901 --> 40:27.903
I--I didn't want to tell you
that I'd failed.

40:27.947 --> 40:29.644
- You didn't fail, Jessica.

40:29.688 --> 40:32.386
- No, I made a promise
to save your home

40:32.430 --> 40:34.040
and I couldn't make it happen.

40:35.041 --> 40:37.609
- No, come on.
Come inside.

40:37.652 --> 40:40.046
- Not tonight.

40:40.960 --> 40:44.354
- Are you sure?
- Yeah. Jeff is waiting for me.

40:44.398 --> 40:46.574
Um...

40:46.618 --> 40:47.923
another night?

40:49.795 --> 40:51.753
- Okay.

41:01.981 --> 41:04.810
- You got a death wish.

